title: Silver Green Hotel
address: No.9 ANawYaHtar Road, Yangon
descriptions: Simply decorated rooms in an unpretentious hotel offering a restaurant with city views.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"John12312","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This is an average hotel with standard lobby. Rooms were good, clean and well equipped. Breakfast was great, with omelettes cooked to order as well as the usual buffet fare. Front Service/ 3 Stars - have to wait extra 35 min after 2 pm check-in time in order to get my room, no greeting when guests in or out. I have to greet good morning first.

Room/ 3 Stars - made a reservation with a confirmation of Premier room with king bed size in advance but they gave me twin joint bed, normally I won’t have any problem either King or twins Zipped bed however under the twin zipped bed, they placed normal sponge sheets which very hot and uncomfortable to sleep on. When I complained they said it was their standard.

Room Cleanliness/ 2 stars - a lot of previous guests hair (all type of hair) in under the floor and a lot of dust on the table. Extra pillow also very dirty, there was still on spot of stained on pillow, Look like a stained of human sperm.

When I called Front office staff and show him how bad the room was arranged, they finally switch with another but have to wait 3 more hours to be able to move to new room. Breakfast/ 3 Stars - normal, not much choice.

Bellman - leaked of concentration. I was waiting for grab and when the grab arrived with another passengers, he opened the door for those passengers and when I was able to go in, he just closed the door. I was shocked for a second.

Hotel Location is Great which surrounding with restaurants.

Suggest: please train the housekeepers well, ohh need to train the supervisor first. Every room comes with a large  balcony overlooking the golf course. The deluxe room was very spacious and furnished tastefully. The bathroom had clean fluffy towels and the tree hugger in me was happy to see mini refillable toiletry bottles. The only eyesore was the plastic water bottles which could have been replaced with glass water bottles and a water refill station.

The breakfast buffet for the 3 mornings that we were there was a huge disappointment. The coffee left a salty aftertaste, the bread selection was minimal, no pancakes or waffles, and croissants were doled out only when asked. However, the croissants tasted heavenly.

The food at the restaurant by the pool (oasis) was excellent. We loved everything that we ordered from there. The restaurant at the hotel has smaller selection of food.

The pool is huge with beautiful green area to hang out/read/play games in even if you are not swimming.

We had an excellent time and would definitely  go back even if i don't like the breakfast 😄 because the view and the service provided by the staff is worth overlooking the not so good  breakfast","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Seng H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Received a gift voucher from my sis-in-law to stay at a Gary Player Suite. The rooms are wide and clean - the bathroom as well. Loved taking a shower there. The view is fantastic and it's just so relaxing to lie on the bed, take in the golf course scenery and just use your phone on the bed. Nice to chill. Although the hotel provided mosquito repellent liquid, mosquitoes just won't die there.||It is a nice getaway place and there is a bar and a restaurant on the ground floor of the hotel. The lobby is in the open space, so you can just relax there with the cool breeze coming in from the golf course. ||I will blame Covid19 for not being able to enjoy a buffet breakfast at the hotel restaurant. The waiters just gave us a set menu to choose from. Try the Healthy Breakfast set. It is by far the best menu there. Not many guests during the Covid19 period but the waiters forgot to serve us coffee which was imcluded in the set menu.||Conclusion: a nice quiet place to just chill (nothing else), there are two other restaurants / cafes nearby... and most importantly, prepare your own mosquito repellent spray, especially in the Monsoon Season as the mosquitoes are no joke!!","Images":null,"When":""}]

But it is a good choice for the night before take an early flight.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jesse Medlong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVsJ0X9buOrLtMdNh3VVgfgGD08ZPxyTDeor9mjIYMuv0aWJd9l=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I enjoyed my stay at the hotel.
For international guests, you will need to present your passport upon checking in. They will make a photo copy of it.

They cleaned up the room every day for us. Be aware that you need to turn a switch on for the hot water. You must use your room key or the paper tag on the complimentary water and place it in the slot next to the light switches to turn everything on in the room.

The continental breakfast is from 7am - 10am. Breakfast is the same thing every morning. You can order a breakfast to go in the morning (it's just a sandwich and bottled water).

You may leave your room key at the front desk for the day if you would like. You may have to have the room key reprogrammed throughout your stay if you're there for a while.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"zillusia100","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QcqjfyADTZteN6UQjkfmI_GEkLkHcE0ELlx5mF7J8mlJ0xtKNb2Z0W14ZGUWvDdJggyxw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"My 1st my impression of this hotel was good. So I recommended my friends to check in as well. But the hotel continues to disappoint a 2nd consecutive time. How can this hotel allow overbooking of rooms and expect affected guest to compromise either to a lower quality hotel or to expect us to just combine our rooms? If the basic honoring of guest's booking can so easily be comprised, how can we ever trust this hotel again? To make things worse, we even went down personally to the hotel a few days before our check in date to ensure the hotel has our booking correctly received due to the prior similar incident happened in December 2018 when the hotel also says no room for us after we booked the rooms. Then now for the 2nd time suddenly say they have offered our rooms to other guests upon check in again? If this is genuinely an oversight, then I suggest the owner of the hotel to either train your staff properly or review if the stuff is suitable to represent your hotel.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tin Maung H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I booked a Junior Suite as I liked the description in Agoda. title: LOTTE HOTEL YANGON
address: 82 Sin Phyu Shin Avenue, Yangon 11091
descriptions: Refined hotel featuring indoor & outdoor pools, plus dining, a cocktail lounge & lake views.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Sandhya Tamang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-Z1P6Raag8kMSHKxzLpdF7qW-PtPUa5EbZx2dVHrDPCUBUqfemA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Location-wise, it is convenient for people coming directly from the airport.
The room itself was clean, though the carpets seemed a bit worn. The staff service was satisfactory but not exceptional for a 5-star hotel.
The hotel also offers both indoor and outdoor pools, catering to guests who prefer swimming in different settings.

DO NOT BUY THE CLUB LOUNGE UNLESS THEY BRING IMPROVEMENTS: The club lounge experience was shocking, as the food provided was insufficient, especially during tea n talk time. Tea N Talk includes 2 mini cakes and a mini plate of pizza (they call it pizza but its a tiny mini sushi hahaha)This is a significant area that needs attention. The club lounge is also not worth it because no one buys it and as a result, they come up with sushi looking pizza menu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFg5HM9_qmdMpBs-YSrfnw_W32qKQrU4ROnDgI&fid=0x0:0x1ce0d39a47ca647c"],"When":"2025-2-16"},{"Name":"aung ko ko Win","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKSLsCXVULCVlKDvsIVUBinTNszcYRk6xB_IHPuznv_6kk2Hmc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently had the pleasure of enjoying tea time at the Lotte Hotel and it was quite the experience. The cake was absolutely excellent, with a rich, flavorful taste, and the plating was beautiful—definitely a treat for the eyes as well as the taste buds.

However, the Americano coffee left a bit to be desired. The taste was rather light, and I feel the coffee could have been stronger to match the high standard of the other offerings.

The venue itself is spacious and comfortable, providing a welcoming atmosphere for a relaxing break. The staff were very friendly and attentive, offering great service throughout.

Parking was convenient, and although the price is on the higher end, it’s expected for an international hotel. Overall, a lovely experience, though I would recommend improving the coffee.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO0v7TPbn1NyxNUsQ8DEVFMOqvRe5YGnf8HNa3H&fid=0x0:0x1ce0d39a47ca647c"],"When":"2025-2-11"},{"Name":"Dmitri M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qczn4VDfUM6-AtEt-6oaNazFa-i9Fy6kqPVfGIlPil6vJulEYyK8t930jZwOW4hD80mzw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Excellent hotel. Very pleasant outdoor pool by the lake. I have not tried their food, as it appears to be rather exorbitantly priced by Burmese standards, but the menu of the hotel's several restaurants is quite extensive.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tun Ko Naing","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL1GMb43qTj6dUFuhDbM2ujmy4nMwOAozoT_mS0jy9mnkF9rA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Hotel provided an exceptional venue for the Medical CME Seminar I attended. The highlight of the day was the grand dinner—an exquisite culinary experience featuring a wide variety of gourmet dishes, beautifully presented and bursting with flavor. The elegant setting, combined with impeccable service, made it a memorable evening of networking and relaxation.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"ZtablE","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIr9Si6eCfbvJM-2BX2J14RU1xOmKhuRdSj899cXUSkfwXKHmU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I spent 3 nights there and I appreciate what staffs treated me so well, beautiful hotel with good location, good foods which I almost gave 5 stars.

However, on my last night (~8pm) I heard housekeepers (more than 1 person talked together) knocked on my room door during my toilet time so I cannot open for them. After seconds, they opened room door with master key and tried to opened restroom door. So, I pushed restroom back and told them to stop directly. Housekeepers told me that they would like to make-up my room (even I press “do not disturb” already). Then I told them back no need to clean now.

Since, the hotel rooms has double-lock with chain but I didn’t use it. I just recommend visitors that do not forget to use double-lock to prevent this situation occur.

Overall, 5 minus 1 from this issue so I would give 4 stars.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMZ5vtIZFqw5pvZ4_e4CeaNkTIhPa9hSu_w9g94&fid=0x0:0x1ce0d39a47ca647c"],"When":"2024-12-18"},{"Name":"Trip.com Member","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Spacious room. Very friendly and helpful staff. The room was very clean, just the floor could be a little bit cleaner. One tube in the bathroom was leacking. There were 2 towels per person, a comfortable bed,  a small table with a chair, 2 bottles of water and we got a welcome drink when we arrived :) Also there is a TV and an air conditioning which was working but apparently it was not possible to adjust the temperature. The free breakfast included 2 slices of toasted toast, 1 fried egg, butter and jam, a coffee and a banana. Free WiFi was working at the ground floor. Thats where the negatives stop. ||||Firstly lets put this in perspctive,our room cost 63 usd (20 bucks each) including a very nice breakfast. ||||On arrival we were greeted with an orange juice and taken to our room by 3 porters lugging our bags up 4 stories to our room. The breakfast is great and they even remember if you like ketchip or chilli sauce and your choice of fruit the next day. The eggs are perfect!||||On the last night I sat and watched football with the local guys on a 40" TV and we had a great laugh whilst I ate my excellent 3 dollar special fried rice packed with chicken, pork, prawns...that I had no chance of finishing due to the volume.||||All in all a fantastic place which is 15 mins from airport and anything else in the city. title: Hotel 9 Mile
address: V4JP+CRV Hotel 9 Mile, Tsp, No. 3/A (10/12/14), Taw Win, 1 Street, Yangon
user_reviews: [{"Name":"Michael B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This hotel is modestly priced ($50 double/twin, $60 double/twin with balcony, including breakfast) yet has exceptionally high standards. Just one year old (Oct 2015) it is in pristine condition and kept spotless throughout. Air conditioned bedrooms are spacious and have all you need. The beds are extremely comfortable with duvets and white linen and fresh towels are provided daily. The bathroom has a walk-in shower and there is always plenty of hot water. Staff are delightful and extremely helpful and the manager Zayar is always eager to oblige. We asked for coffees in our room one day and he immediately sent up a kettle with sachets of coffee, creamer and sugar - all complimentary. Breakfast is included - either Korean (the hotel is Korean owned, hence the excellent management) or Anerican (eggs, toast, fruit, coffee).  The restaurant serves only Korean food at lunch and dinner, but there are plenty of other restaurants nearby.||The hotel is in a quiet location, and is a little challenging to find at first (ask for Nine Mile Road at Ocean Centre and turn off this road at the Corola Hotel). The hotel is only a few minutes drive from the airport and pickups can be arranged for just 5000 kyats (about $4) which saves you haggling with local taxi drivers. ||I had been staying at another nearby hotel which I have used for years but standards were declining so moved to Hotel 9 Mile on the recommendation of a local friend. I didn't regret the move at all. The hotel is incredible value!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Steven L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Stayed 12 days. My main complain is the WIFI. It goes on and off. Even as we were leaving, they were still fixing the WIFI by installing a complete new system. The room is reasonably furnished but nothing fancy. Room size is big. Window view is that of a shower stall. Bathroom is a perpetural flood every time you take a shower. Breakfast is either Korean or American. I love the Korean breakfast. There is a massage parlor on site. Tried it but didn't like. They tend to grind your muscle against your bone. I thought that was not very good for the body. Otherwise price is reasonable. It is very difficult to communicate with the girls at the counter. They do not understand much English. I kept asking them to stop opening the window when they clean the room in the morning because of the mosquito but they do not seem to understand what I said. The manager speaks excellent English and is very helpful. Taxi fare to down town or anywhere for that matter is always 5000. Foreigners are taken advantage of because local pay much less (\u003e2000). It seems that it also applied to drinks and food too. Small mini fridge as per normal and small safe box,which was not functioning unfortunately were provided. There was small little tv with 3 channels ridiculously. Breakfast were served with two varieties, American breakfast and Korean breakfast. I tried American and it was simple dish and nothing special. I noticed i was the only non-korean in the dinning room and whole hotel i guess. Hence, this hotel can be considered as Korean hotel. That's the beauty of the place being so close.||||I had dinner at the restaurant.  This hotel mainly caters to Koreans who come to Yangon for golf excursions.  The Korean food was amazing.  Even the kimchee was true, original Korean made.||||The bed, like all of Myanmar, is hard.  But, I got used to it as we stayed at 7 hotels throughout our travel from 3* to 5*.||||I went to the Spa and had an 75 min massage.  The girls are quite young.....16-19 year olds.  The massage is a Thai style massage where they would manipulate your back and go through all kinds of contortions.  The beds are laid out very close to each other so you could hear the next person beside you.  It was only 10,000 which is about $12.00 US.  Amazing.  No wonder it is a very popular place.||||The staff is very friendly, service oriented and on the ball.  I paid $45 US for the night and was a happy camper. Thank you Hotel 9 Mile.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Heidi M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdcKHisBXAOJmIugCgnKbcAscQkQI1t40WdQAMXk1g3ttzWj18FtKnHxNeSUm5OfHPMtQ=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Our guide suggested we end our Burmese vacation with massages at a spa near the airport before our departure flight, and it was the perfect way to end our vacation and adventure in Myanmar!  Don't be fooled by the modest appearance, the facility is clean and the staff are very friendly and accommodating.  Like many Asian massages, you are not required to undress, and no oils are used.  But be warned, this is no Swedish Massage!  You are in for a treat if you're looking for a deep tissue massage that incorporates pressure points and stretching.  My masseuse not only massaged my entire body for 90 minutes, but she walked on my back, used her arms, legs and feet to maximize the impact, and stretched my arms, legs, back and neck.  All this for $15USD...unheard of!!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"THEREE OHHW","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXliPRdggWK4MBtVeoCPy2Y3MNWfcs1hrsDx9jx4MJ93AkcJj2k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Impressive hotel. It felt like I had my home office again. The hotel does not look like much from the outside but when you come in it is like a MUSEUM! So many contemporary art pieces.

I enjoyed my stay here a lot. The facilities and amenities were well kept, I would argue this was the fanciest hotel I have been to in Myanmar by price. The amenities feel like it is at least 3.5 star, but this hotel is actually just a 2 star.

Electricity is always on 24/7 and the internet is pretty decent. I had zoom calls without much lag!

One downside though is every service here is EXPENSIVE. Laundry, food, breakfast are all above average priced. The only saving grace is that they give you free airport transfers. But I guess that is their business model, cheap brief layover stays.

Also, they tried to keep my passport safe for me in a folder. I didn't appreciate that at all, they should have brought me my passport back as soon as they didn't need it! I had to ask for it back...

Finally, the location (aside from being close to the airport) is horrible. Only 2 restaurants are nearby and they are both average at best, with one being better because if pricing. No convinient stores at all, you can't buy snacks or any thing else you need like shampoo without taking a taxi to the middle of the city.

Overall it was a good stay, I would comeback again a day before my next flight out of Myanmar. bar is a little dull with few people but awesome for someone wants to be quiet.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOG0gf2EP1MioZkUYBVrmHoTY6f6QQlYkwy-gTY&fid=0x0:0x3e371c6cd19fff83"],"When":"2024-5-23"},{"Name":"Kenneth Duan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWIYaQoqDvyRFKa66rsi-1V0Kp-wSc9QKiqxxfrwLgcwmd5gnbO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My stay at the Riverview Hotel was a blend of highs and lows, resulting in a middling rating of three stars out of five. While the hotel boasted some commendable aspects, there were also notable areas that fell short of expectations.

Upon arrival, I was greeted by a courteous receptionist who efficiently checked me in. The lobby exuded a sophisticated ambiance with its modern decor and comfortable seating areas. However, the check-in process felt slightly disorganized, with a longer wait time than anticipated.

Entering my room, I was initially impressed by its cleanliness and spacious layout. The bed was comfortable, and the linens appeared fresh. However, upon closer inspection, I noticed some signs of wear and tear, such as scuff marks on the furniture and a few stains on the carpet. Additionally, the room lacked certain amenities that are becoming standard in many hotels, such as a coffee maker and mini-fridge.

The bathroom, while adequately sized, had outdated fixtures and could benefit from a renovation. The water pressure in the shower was inconsistent, alternating between strong bursts and weak dribbles. Furthermore, the toiletries provided were of subpar quality, failing to meet the standard expected from a hotel of this caliber.

One of the highlights of my stay was the hotel's dining options. The breakfast buffet offered a variety of delicious dishes, ranging from traditional favorites to international selections. The restaurant staff were attentive and accommodating, ensuring a pleasant dining experience. However, the prices were on the higher side, and I felt that the value for money could have been better.

The hotel's amenities left much to be desired. While there was a fitness center available, it was small and poorly equipped. Additionally, the pool area was underwhelming, with limited seating and a lack of ambiance. It seemed as though these facilities were an afterthought rather than a focal point of the hotel's offerings.

In terms of location, the Riverview Hotel was conveniently situated near several attractions and transportation options. However, the surrounding area was noisy, especially at night, which detracted from the overall tranquility of the stay. Furthermore, parking was limited and expensive, adding an extra inconvenience for guests with vehicles.

On the service front, the staff were generally friendly and helpful, although there were instances where communication was lacking. For example, requests made to the front desk were sometimes forgotten or took longer than expected to fulfill. Additionally, housekeeping could be inconsistent, with some days seeing thorough cleanings while others left much to be desired.

Overall, my experience at the Riverview Hotel was a mixed bag. While there were aspects to appreciate, such as the dining options and cleanliness of the rooms, there were also notable shortcomings, including outdated facilities and inconsistent service. With some improvements in these areas, the hotel has the potential to elevate its rating and provide a more satisfying experience for guests.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ko Kyaw","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXk3SOvIliN7feYgaUVVkur6fMkjVbC2q0sbZDoKcRXWKV7QYwoCw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very well decorated. The driver is always chewing on something ghastly and spit quite often, horrible. For such a good hotel has anyone seen the bed sheets, maybe one should before even sitting on it. Maybe people who are giving such good reviews are used to sleep on dirty beds. Anyway to cut the talk short, watch what you eat and don't be a fool.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dinesh kumar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_GuDRTv1WgjN1nG59cJbQ5XBwhgOcvyBTy3ErbwqA6oUWZWG3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"New review 2019:

The hotel has been upgraded with the same excellent service as before. The rooms are clean and maintained well. They even have an ATM in the lobby. There is a 24hour CityMart (local supermarket) nearby. Since the hotel is on the main road, you can easily get Grab (like Uber car sharing service) and go around the city.

Do read my previous review below:

*****************************
Old review from 2017 below:

We stayed in the hotel for 3 nights in the Superior twin room and 2 nights in the Junior Suite B with Bathtub. As most of the reviews have already mentioned,  choose the rooms towards the back of the hotel (away from the road) and preferably to the right (facing east), these rooms have a better view and also you will get a glimpse of the rising sun. The hotel's buffet breakfast is great and each day they have a special local cuisine. This, in my opinion, would be a very safe way to try out the local dishes. The staff can speak English and are very friendly. The rooms are clean and we'll  maintained. The only problem is  that the doors do not appear to be sound proof and could be a problem if there are a lot of guests moving in-and-out of their rooms. TIP: There is a City Mart outlet straight down the road, about 15mins walk. There is a hospital nearby. There are some great food places in about 15mins walk.  (Note: photos are from the Junior Suite B room #403)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNTRys335Gz8GYnI6YYBqGeugAo2Gk_wDNJK7Uv&fid=0x0:0x2c8d2472717556e6"],"When":"2018-1-7"},{"Name":"Sandy’s Shine","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXd9XwYaXMx0VXxehGbmy_BXGG7o4D1R7qOLglJAXom2nLJ9IM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best technology in the leather industry","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ian Borja","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUNLX_Fs9Bq4tJkkoiCk_V6a2wYuYVowqo_cuP2tYcQNCXRug1DBw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Small hotel of about 20 rooms. They do have good bed sheets, nice cozy room, very clean toilet and bathroom, and their towels are nice too.

They also have a simple buffet breakfast but would surely be filling. They have the normal fried rice, noodles, veggies, fishball, mominga, congee, bread, coffee & tea, different spreads, cereal, juice and fruits.

All staff, including the owner James, are very friendly  and they will make sure you will have the best stay.

Downside is location is in a main highway, but the noise is bearable. It is located a bit far from downtown area. Cab fare though is very inexpensive in Myanmar especially if you use Grab. If you let the front desk of the hotel book your Grab ride, you will even get a.discount.

i spent 9 nights there.
we booked our room  2 weeks in advanced and we paid
2 days(Room Rate) deposit already. the price we agreed upon was 40000 kyats per night. it was all fine  for 7 days. after that  they charged me 5000 kyats more for each of 2 days due to high season and stuff.
im fine with paying 10000 kyats more but they didnt mention that before we book our room. it was a shambolic decision made by room division department. Im also in a hotel industry in EU. i have never faced those kind of actions.
they need to improved and the reception staffs should be more informed.","Images":null,"When":""}]

descriptions: Unfussy rooms in a laid-back budget hotel offering free breakfast, plus gardens & a restaurant.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Kyaw Win Aung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUsYi36TFyxJ-LIo2MhhQEBs9xJE4h6IFeDZRFnA3e_OF91nTtE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Room is comfortable, accommodation with aircon and bathroom is fair enough. Our check in was easy and friendly. We were so happy with the room it was immaculately clean & spacious. It has a TV, mini bar and kettle which are all very useful! |It has a nice big bath room and super hot shower. |What made our stay particularly special were the staff all the maids and porters have been very smiley & friendly. I'm very grateful to the owner who went out of his way to help us with where to go while in Yangon & also where to continue our trip. |The lady at breakfast was lovely too, we had toast and fruit for the first couple of days but I'd recommend trying the Burmese coconut chicken noodle soup very tasty! |The location is out of the main city it's quite peaceful and it is in walking distance to the lake, it's also continent for the airport.|There are lots of nice places to eat nearby too. |It's excellent value for money, I'd definitely return! |Thanks very much :)","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Georgiana F","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdHDxxyBDO6igPA51sqxYAI1TTeuGvapT1sWSCJfPSgzOZltNlMhWmUDpj2A3v7zAw89g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I lived here for five months, March-July. It's a charming place with staff that go out if their way to be helpful. Breakfast is included. Mary will accommodate you as best she can with your breakfast preferences. I often order the fried vermicelli for dinner which the staff will bring to your room. The lodge is away from traffic and quiet with lots of greenery about. It's not a touristy place. You can't walk out the door to go shopping. But taxis are readily available to take you wherever you want to go. The front desk will help you with this. There is rudimentary laundry service. No dry cleaning. The air conditioning is wonderful. There are normal complimentary items like coffee, tea, bottled water, shampoo, soap, toothbrush. The lodge is past its glory days, but it's still got lots off charm to offer. The staff is a large part of that charm.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Anthony S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This hotel has surpassed my expectation massively. The room is extremely clean, the air conditioning is not at all loud and very efficient. The bathroom is brilliant, and instant hot water!||The tv has about 6 English channels which is more than enough, the minibar is well stacked and well priced.||The laundry service is fast and very reasonably priced, and the breakfast is great, good omlettes and fresh fruit!||And on top of that the staff are amazing, they will happily book a taxi for you and get cheaper non-tourist rates, also the owner gave us a lot of help deciding what to do here going above and beyond what we expected, which has really pleased us and made our stay that extra bit more pleasant and personal.||The staff are very attentive too, and try to make your stay as comfy as possible.||Great place, for an awesome price, very quite, and out of the city so no traffic noise and lots of wildlife to keep you entertained outside.||The ONLY complaint bieng extremely picky besides the occasional powercut is in heavy rain the metal roof makes a bit of a racket. Didn't bother me at all but light sleepers might want a different room in monsoon season.||How this isn't higher rates is absolutely beyond me!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kate W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdCjMUwIiBikRhCLHgN_0vyGAo1GvT8DEukiKQb1ujC_eFsFjYrQ0OvLoSxPtqmCdgvFA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I chose Highland Lodge for the affordable price and proximity to the airport for a one-night stay before an onward flight.  I was very pleasantly surprised by the friendly family feel and quiet, leafy setting.  ||||My request for an airport pick up was dealt with quickly and for a very reasonable price.  All of the staff spoke basic English and a couple were fluent - and very patient with my useless attempts to speak Burmese!  A simple but good breakfast featured fresh fruit and eggs. ||||The rooms were simple with beautiful hardwood floors looking out over a leafy courtyard.  The bathroom decoration was slightly dated but all in perfect working order and instant hot water.  Everything was spotlessly clean.  The wifi in Myanmar has a reputation for being a bit on-off but I found better reception across the country than I have at home in rural England.  ||||Highland Lodge is a bit of a trek to downtown Yangon so I would probably stay closer to town for a longer stay, but they provided a lovely welcome for my first night in Myanmar and a million times better than your usual impersonal airport hotel.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Myo Thant","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJuko0pnrYJwLLprNZvzxion3_Xftwkk8bk69_5QIKtTT5VWg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It is great.

Instead of staying in small rooms in downtown with heavy traffic and pollution, this is one of the best place and good rates.
Very clean and surrounding is so pleasant. Travelling around is easy. Taxi to downtown is around $6 USD only. Buses are also available","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Eve Baker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9xOV1ddwicNg0fxmU09hgyY3I2SNB34v8QnhdjaeKOHr-nQjH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I cannot rate this place highly enough. Thanks very much!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Georgiana F","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdHDxxyBDO6igPA51sqxYAI1TTeuGvapT1sWSCJfPSgzOZltNlMhWmUDpj2A3v7zAw89g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"My review is posted elsewhere. title: Diamond Lake Hotel
address: 437 Min Gyi St, Yangon
user_reviews: [{"Name":"kevinbeal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdGDJ6WBs5CBoNVcQAwShh25kntoFa0rN3szxhkmmJHnXagNPuSfO1BRpzbnKc5wyCe_g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I have been here for 10 days. This hotel just opened. The first few days were good. However things are changing fast. They allow smoking everyplace in the building. It is disgusting! Smell of smoke everywhere. Ashes on the floor in elevator,main lobby, carpeted hallways. They should have no smoking in these areas and have certain rooms that are for smoking. It wont be long before the nice rooms here are destroyed from the smoke. Room service started out well. However three days they failed to clean my room. I had to remind them on each of these days. One day even after reminding them they didn't bother cleaning. Breakfast buffet started out well with a girl serving coffee. This came to a end and it was help yourself. The food taste good but small selection. Some morning they didn't even have eggs or bread because the staff forgot to get it. They have air condition in the eating area however they never turned it on once. Your shirt is soaking wet by the time your done eating. Some days they didn't even open the windows. One elevator is already broke so it's a long wait to get to your room. This could be a great hotel but they need to make changes! The smoking is the biggest problem at this place!!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alvin R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We were in town for nearly two weeks before the grand opening.  Our hosts negotiated a rate of 30,000K (about $23US) with the understanding that there would be limited services and no wi-fi or breakfast available during our stay.  This was acceptable to us, as all we needed was a basic and clean hotel, and this gave us a chance to stay in a really nice hotel at a reasonable cost.  We understand that the regular room rate would be $50US, and include breakfast and free wi-fi, after it was officially open.  It is a step above a budget hotel, but not quite what I would call a luxury hotel.  The staff was attentive to our needs whenever we requested anything.||||We had room 612, which was impeccably clean, spacious, and worth even the regular the cost.  We had maid service every day except the day before our checkout, which was their grand opening day.  (Apparently they were so busy with the grand opening that they forgot us.)||||There is only one usable electrical outlet, at the bedside night stand.  It would have been nice to have other outlets, especially near the bathroom to plug in electric razors. Tip: consider bringing an extension cord.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"vicky m","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QcLvGDdMkm_athQbRQtTYCQxjNUnlrxzopfUA8yGN0YYBZmB4uuNayh0HxTR0N7aNnuMg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I think we were one of the first to stay at the hotel. There was lots of staff and they were very helpful. The rooms were clean and everything was new. The air-con worked great and views were great. When we were there they weren't serving breakfast but next time that will be apart of our cost. The cost is much better than many of the hotels downtown and by the airport. This hotel and service was an upgrade to some others I've stayed in Yangon with the price being better here. We plan on staying here and recommending it to others.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"mark s","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QftlnsLB8VReEIa8q3x-FUIWL9jAVnw9OiPzFml0xLx7k1DporKgZdMXGALflbNzntF3w=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Never found a decent hotel in this price range near the airport until we found the Diamond Lake hotel. Now, always stay here when arriving Yangon after dark and before early departures. Bookable online but pay in cash 50 usd. Or book direct, ask for discount. Location is a nice, quiet neighborhood, stroll to local businesses and restaurants. High floors, with views, on one side can see airport tower, yet no plane noise audible. Breakfast and access to their disco karaoke included. It would get highest rating but they need better (and more romantic) lighting in the rooms.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Paul R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qd0Gzx7-o-W0qn7F-oHhorx-ann6UFYRniBmE7Ar1MhRFtO-x6vY7U2LNCPC1lcQidkpw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I stayed at Diamond Lake hotel for 4 nights - mainly because the hotel was within walking distance to a family I was visiting. The staff were very courteous and friendly.||||I would have rated this hotel as VERY GOOD but I am going to rate it as AVERAGE for one main reason.  The Wi-Fi service they have provided me as plain VERY SLOW - it was garbage and this NOT acceptable for this day and age.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alvin R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We had stayed here in February, 2017, and wrote the first Trip Advisor review for this hotel, and had planned to stay here again during our next visit in January, 2018.  This time, it was a disappointment.  They had just opened an adult type business that took entire two floors above the lobby floor, and that business spilled over into other rooms throughout the hotel.  Let's just say we saw sights and heard sounds in the elevators, hallways, and nearby rooms that would be good if we could unsee and unhear.  We decided to leave the next morning, before breakfast, and stay elsewhere..||||Do not take children here.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Thang Tin Lian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU7HHh9H0MsuywqR9676IVLGGme1TkNOBlef5wLAJiN4Jas3ZRg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The Hotel is just fine as others, the Apple Bar and KTV is also incredible. user_reviews: [{"Name":"chuenel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QejddW0yoGeT8LnCjh-OGQgsf6YKqhof3HZA5-um4yCkQej85oCdMUmKPJmnowcu5Ag5w=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We stayed at this hotel for one night as we had an early morning flight out of Yangon the next day. Given that the price (USD 30) was quite competitive for hotels near Yangon airport, and even though there were no Tripadvisor reviews available so far, we gave this place a chance. Unfortunately, we cannot recommend this hotel.||The hotel is located next to a major road while the windows do not absorb much of the noise produced by the heavy traffic and the constant honking. Not the very best combination... When we arrived, we felt like staying in a tent in the middle of a freeway… Luckily, the traffic became less at night which means we slept better than expected.||One of the reasons we booked this hotel is that it seemd to be quite new. When we arrived, one of the receptionist confirmed that the hotel had been open for 8 months only. However, the bathroom in our room looked as if it had been in use for many years already.||The staff was quite friendly. However, as they only spoke very little English, it was difficult to communicate with them. The hotel seems to be frequented by Chinese guests – maybe the staff speaks Chinese.||When we arrived, we asked the staff to arrange a taxi to take us to the airport the next morning. The staff confirmed that a taxi will be arranged for MMK 5,000 (which is rather much for Yangon standards given that the ride was supposed to take no more than 15 minutes). The next morning, a taxi was ready to pick us up but asked that we pay MMK 7,000. The taxi ride took a little more than 15 minutes. As there was almost no traffic at 6:00 am, expect considerably more than that during rush hour.||Overall, our experience at Bayint Naung Hotel was not the very best one. There must be better options to stay at close to Yangon airport.||","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sayar T Excellent","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUa7_hZYPPBph0OaMwrJnMkvl5xh9IVH1qbngqPKCVfZ-1corE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I would like to say not bad but it needs much in all round to be able to catch up with international .","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Thura Aung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWNP7_wbRz8c8C9iXucAqAFL67pYZYvtvrUdMSUKsqKOcYB3pqa=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Awesome Place and nice to stay. title: Wishton Hotel
address: No.365, Thitsar Road and Shwe Thitsar Street (Corner),No.13 Ward, Yangon
descriptions: Relaxed hotel featuring straightforward quarters with balconies, plus a gym, a cafe/bar & breakfast.
complete_address: {"borough":"","street":"No.365, Thitsar Road and Shwe Thitsar Street (Corner),No.13 Ward","city":"Yangon","postal_code":"","state":"","country":"MM"}
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ako Linn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU81170LiobW34fSs6lQEhLyYMbtcDoKGDvyr6wzh9z0OFovXdt3w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I would be happy to write a review of Japanese hospitality in Myanmar!

Japanese hospitality, also known as "omotenashi," is known for its attention to detail, sincerity, and warmth. During my recent trip to Myanmar, I had the pleasure of experiencing this hospitality firsthand at a Japanese-owned hotel.

From the moment I arrived, I was greeted with a warm smile and a refreshing welcome drink. The staff went above and beyond to make sure that my stay was comfortable and enjoyable. They were always available to answer any questions I had and to provide recommendations for things to see and do in the area.

One of the things that stood out to me was the attention to detail. The room was immaculate, with every amenity I could possibly need, from a comfortable bed to a well-stocked minibar. The hotel also offered a range of complimentary services, including a daily breakfast.

But what really made my stay special was the warmth and sincerity of the staff. They truly seemed to care about my well-being and went out of their way to make me feel at home. Whether it was a friendly conversation in the lobby or a kind gesture like a the staff always made me feel welcome and valued.

Overall, I would highly recommend this Japanese-owned hotel to anyone visiting Myanmar. The combination of Japanese hospitality and Myanmar's natural beauty and culture made for an unforgettable experience. Thank you to the staff for making my stay so memorable!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jamie O","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I stayed for one month at Wishton while working at Myanmar Plaza. Every day it was a joy to come back to this clean and elegant hotel. The staff were very warm and friendly - from the porters up to the management.||||I stayed in a superior double room. The size was great. A lot of space to hang clothes as well as shelves, which meant I didn't have to live out of my suitcase.||||The bathroom was modern and efficient. The strong water-pressure and instant hot water made the shower a wonderful experience. The bath was nice and spacious as well.||||The wifi was good, being better at night for some reason. I connected my Apple TV to the flat screen in the room and had no connectivity issues. Video calls with New Zealand also ran smoothly.||||Breakfast was a highlight every day. Prepared by Japanese chefs, the numerous and varied options were always fresh and of good quality. Again, the staff were friendly and more than happy to assist, even asking me if I had any special requests. Sure enough, my bacon was waiting for me the next morning.||||The hotel has a restaurant, gym and underground parking lot. It is a quick and convenient taxi ride away from Myanmar Plaza. Nearby eating options depend on your willingness to "go local."||||All in all, I had a fantastic experience at Wishton and would happily stay there again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alan Chang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVAqn0TX1dB9zDcfXaCBm_KsnLYug-3tc5zISPjeWOymioUhY8ceg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"In my other home in Myanmar, the Japanese-style service and quality are very clean and reliable.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Walter Khun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXfJu-h7YJypCZ9v22D7CGfLrEFm-rouNRXWjsqUE3YBAxOEpMT=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great place for short-stay, long-stay with competitive corporate rate or reason discount.
